article.description: — Dylan Painter had 20 points as Delaware beat Northeastern 82-76 in overtime on Monday night.
article.headline: Painter carries Delaware past Northeastern 82-76 in OT
article.linkText: Painter carries Delaware past Northeastern 82-76 in OT
article.story: BOSTON -- — Dylan Painter had 20 points as Delaware beat Northeastern 82-76 in overtime on Monday night. Andrew Carr had 18 points for Delaware (12-6, 3-2 Colonial Athletic Association). Ebby Asamoah added 16 points and eight rebounds. Kevin Anderson had 13 points and nine assists. Shaquille Walters scored a career-high 23 points for the Huskies (6-11, 0-6), who have lost seven consecutive games. Jahmyl Telfort added 16 points. Nikola Djogo had 15 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
